description: The Mongchon History Museum was opened in 1992. It mainly displays the old Baekje culture sites and ancient tombs, including the Han River Valley, as well as the Mongchon Tucheng ruins model and relics. The History Museum is not very big, with only one floor. It is a closed tour route. After entering the entrance of the exhibition hall, there are the consultation office, the toilet and the video gallery on the left. In the middle of the hall, there is a dynamic interactive circular sand table of Mengcun Tucheng Cultural Relics Group. After bypassing the circular sand table, the left-hand side is the Fengna Tucheng Cultural Relics Area, the Ancient Living Relics Area, the bricks and tiles of the Three Kingdoms period, the cultural relic experience platform, and Seoul. The Silla Culture, opposite to the Baekje Late Culture Exhibition Area and the Ancient East Asian Cultural Exchange Exhibition Area, will return to the door. What is special is that there is a children's experience area here, and the introduction of the exhibition wall has cute patterns and illustrations, which are especially attractive to children and are very suitable for tourists with children.
